drawings.author: ZWZhNTMzZTE2NzI3
drawings.text: Note to DM: If Krentz survived the fight at the yawning portal, he will be here, in Q5.

drawings.author: ZWZhNTMzZTE2NzI3
drawings.text: Clarification Note to DM: Stairs, indicated by repeated parallel lines that get longer or shorter.  Going up the stairs indicates moving from shorter toward longer lines. Down the stairs is going longer to shorter. For example, going from northwest Q2 toward Q4 moves down the stairs. For clarity, arrows have been added to this map that will always point in the direction that the stairs go "UP."

drawings.author: ZWZhNTMzZTE2NzI3
drawings.text: Turn on light effect in Q11 when Nihiloor/Mind Flayer leaves for nice portal effect.

drawings.author: ZWZhNTMzZTE2NzI3
drawings.text: Note to DM: Core to the module, this dungeon is supposed to be completely dark. The shimmering water lights are there simply for effect, but do provide dim light in the watery sections of hallway. If it is important for you to remain true to the books, right click on those lights and they will turn off.

drawings.author: ZWZhNTMzZTE2NzI3
drawings.text: Note on the underpasses/overpasses: This map contains three parts where sections overlap (e.g. underpass/overpass) each other. We have offered multiple seamless solutions to this. First, if you have the stairway module, you can utilize the included stairways. If not, as your players approach the section of the underpass, you can alternate the open/close nature of the secret doors used to make it a seamless tunnel/hallway experience.
